The freedom this generation enjoys someone fought and died for it. It wasn't free, and it wasn't something Black people had in this country. 
You can't  change something that you didn't create. You can only build on it by fortifying the foundation so that it lasts for the next generation.

@olurinatti Thanks for this. I've watched the first link and I totally get your point, I think we're talking past each other. We both want justice system reform because we know there's not only the American way of doing things. 

And most importantly to my point; just like journalists, even though we know they don't often hold the powerful to account, rather them lie for them like they often do, it's still a good aspiration for journalists to be that, because we know they can.

We should also have similar aspirations for a reformed justice system, rather than looking like we want lawlessness.
